Calculate within-subject OTU correlations

Source: R/NMIT.R
tscor.Rd

This function takes a MultiAssayExperiment and outputs an array of temporal intra-subject correlation matrices.

Usage

tscor(dat, unit_var, method = "kendall", fill_na = 0)

Arguments

dat

A MultiAssayExperiment object specially formatted as an animalcules output.

unit_var

a numeric vector of subject.

method

an option of the correlation method ("pearson", "kendall", "spearman"). The default method is "kendall".

fill_na

a number between 0 and 1 to fill the missing value. The default value is 0.

Value

An three-dimensional array of temporal correlation matrices for each subject.

Author

Yilong Zhang, Huilin Li, Aubrey Odom

Examples

dat <- system.file("extdata/MAE_small.RDS", package = "LegATo") |> readRDS()
output <- tscor(dat, unit_var = "Subject", method = "spearman")
